CSC281 has the course title "Introduction to Cryptography". CSC281 is a 4.0 credit course taught by Muthuramakrishnan Venkitasubramaniam. CSC281 is offered every "Summer Spring Fall ". The modern study of cryptography investigates techniques for facilitating interactions between distrustful entities. In this course we introduce some of the fundamental concepts of this study. Emphasis will be placed on the foundations of cryptography and in particular on precise definitions and proof techniques.(MATH150 or MATH162), AND (CSC171 or prior programming experience)